BIG PLAIN SOLAR, LLC
RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Big Plain Solar, LLC ("Big Plain") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Big Plain generating facility ("Big Plain Facility").
Big Plain is a solar generating facility located in Madison County, Ohio. The Big Plain Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities within the PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM") region.
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Big Plain's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Big Plain Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
Big Plain's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to Big Plain shall be subject to Schedule 2 of PJM's Open Access Transmission Tariff.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $3,904,557.24 The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $325,379.77
